"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody, I'm two weeks out from starting my farmer's market where I'm going to be selling my garden vegetables, and a little bit nervous. I have about 12 cases of fermented cucumber salad that I'm going to sell from spring. I have uh gosh, about uh, you know, quite a bit of baba ganoosh that was from the hot summer. I'm all out of okra, I'm all out of pickled cucumbers. Um, my tomato plants are doing great, and those should come in pretty well. I'm getting a lot of tomatoes right now, but they're just not ready. Two weeks they they will be. Um, and I'll have uh fermented peppers and onions to go with that. That will be a salsa mix. Um I have some herbs I'm gonna try to sell, but really uh I have some issues. I uh my lettuces have not come up. My carrots are doing very poorly. My onions aren't really as uh as spread out. I need to do a better job of planting my seeds and uh closer together next time, creating more of a uh carpet that I will later if I need to trim out and cull. But I need to get a better carpet going uh so that um I can have this and also truthfully, summer extended through October, and we just got our first rain in three weeks or a month uh yesterday or two days ago, and so I'm really hoping that turns things around. But gosh, my cucumbers got eaten alive. I couldn't do anything to keep the uh caterpillars off of them. It was just too hot and too dry, and giving them water from the hose is just not what they're looking for, and they suffered. So I replanted, I'm gonna hopefully get those going. Um, I really would like to get some fall cucumbers, even though I've never had that much luck with fall cucumbers. Spring cucumbers are a different story, but the tomatoes are doing really well. Um, hopefully a lot of these herbs will pick up. Uh before the big rain that just came, I planted everything. I put down a whole bunch more seeds. So hopefully in the next little bit we'll get going, but I'm trying to reassure myself that even if I don't have enough, I'm just going there to talk to people and like uh get into regenerative agriculture, you know, and talking, um, practicing talking with people about regenerative agriculture, figuring out how to say things. And, you know, I learned a lot of that through the farmers market about fermented foods. Uh it eventually I got to the point where I could just open my mouth and all my little phrases would come out. It wasn't really a big deal. So I'm trying to get that way with the regenerative agriculture as well. Anyway, thanks y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody, I'm two weeks out from starting my farmer's market where I'm going to be selling my garden vegetables, and a little bit nervous.\",\n      \"start\": 0.24,\n      \"end\": 8.64,\n      \"duration\": 8.4,\n      \"confidence\": 0.989,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 0.24,\n          \"end\": 0.4,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.993\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 0.4,\n          \"end\": 0.48,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 0.64,\n          \"end\": 0.72,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 0.72,\n          \"end\": 0.96,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ody\",\n          \"start\": 0.96,\n          \"end\": 1.12,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \",\",\n          \"start\": 1.12,\n          \"end\": 1.28,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.89\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" I\",\n          \"start\": 1.28,\n          \"end\": 1.36,\n          \"d